    <title>Apple’s last-gen iPad has dropped to $224 for a limited time</title>
    <content type="html">  

    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="Apple’s ninth-gen iPad on a wooden table, viewed from the top down" src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/2S9XTA6o4eXzfeyh3tztkfVHf0M=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73509279/236563_Apple_iPad_9th_gen_DSeifert_0001.0.jpg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;&lt;em&gt;Two words: headphone jack.&lt;/em&gt; | Photo by Dan Seifert / The Verge&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="3schjp"&gt;Although Apple’s tablet lineup has undergone several shakeups over the last several years, we long considered the &lt;strong&gt;ninth-gen iPad&lt;/strong&gt; to be the &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/23639378/best-ipad-apple-buy-model-price"&gt;best budget iPad&lt;/a&gt; you could get. That changed when Apple &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/7/24151124/apple-ipad-headphone-jack"&gt;dropped the price&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/23418039/apple-ipad-review-10th-gen-2022-10-9-tablet-ipados"&gt;10th-gen iPad&lt;/a&gt; to a more sensible $349 and discontinued its entry-level model. But the 2021 iPad remains a perfectly good slate, especially now that the base model with 64GB of storage is down to a new low of around $224 ($105 off) at &lt;a href="https://www.amazon.com/2021-Apple-10-2-inch-iPad-Wi-Fi/dp/B09G9FPHY6/?tag=theverge02-20" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;Amazon&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://goto.walmart.com/c/482924/565706/9383?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.walmart.com%2Fip%2F2021-Apple-10-2-inch-iPad-Wi-Fi-64GB-Space-Gray-9th-Generation%2F674982024%2F&amp;amp;sharedid=theverge.com" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;Walmart&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href="https://howl.me/cmPKo0JVgxM"&gt;Best Buy&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="c-float-left c-float-hang"&gt;&lt;aside id="pyXor1"&gt;&lt;div data-anthem-component="readmore" data-anthem-component-data='{"stories":[{"title":"The new Apple iPad Air is great —&amp;amp;nbsp;but it’s not the one to get","url":"https://www.theverge.com/24155407/apple-ipad-air-review-2024"},{"title":"Apple announces iPadOS 18 with a built-in calculator and customizable homescreen","url":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24140821/apple-ipados-18-features-updates-apps-wwdc-2024"},{"title":"The OLED iPad Pro was only the beginning for Apple’s return to thin devices","url":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/16/24179598/iphone-17-slim-apple-thinness-ipad-pro-macbook-apple-watch"}]}'&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/aside&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p id="HHXN8t"&gt;As far as hardware is concerned, the ninth-gen iPad is very much a remnant of Apple’s former design language. The 10.2-inch tablet has a traditional iPad look with large bezels, a dedicated home button, and a Lightning port — not to mention a 3.5mm audio jack...&lt;/p&gt;
