    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="wOde9u"&gt;So far, the only way to &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/31/24209910/apple-intelligence-ios-18-preview-siri"&gt;try out Apple Intelligence features&lt;/a&gt; on an iPhone is through the iPhone 15 Pro. The entire iPhone 16 line is expected to get the features this fall, but “you can also bet” the iPhone SE, coming “as early as the beginning of 2025,” will have it too, &lt;a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/newsletters/2024-08-11/iphone-16-preview-bigger-screens-new-colors-camera-button-ai-and-a18-chip-lzpk5495"&gt;says &lt;em&gt;Bloomberg&lt;/em&gt;’s Mark Gurman&lt;/a&gt; in today’s &lt;em&gt;Power On &lt;/em&gt;newsletter&lt;em&gt;. &lt;/em&gt;If that’s true, it could be a lot harder to pass on Apple’s cheapest phone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="96nENd"&gt;The iPhone SE deal has been that you get a cheap, reasonably powerful iPhone that recycles an outdated form factor (&lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/22975531/apple-iphone-se-2022-review-price-specs-screen-battery"&gt;most recently&lt;/a&gt;, the iPhone 8). It’s always been super obvious that it’s Apple’s budget compromise! &lt;/p&gt;
