  &lt;p id="srmUuC"&gt;As you might expect, not every parent wants to outfit their kid with a phone, especially given the rise in cyberbullying and the sheer amount of distractions they pose while in school. Thankfully, the &lt;strong&gt;Fitbit Ace LTE &lt;/strong&gt;is a more pared-down alternative, one that’s matching its all-time low of $199.95 ($30 off) at &lt;a href="https://www.amazon.com/Fitbit-Google-Ace-LTE-Activity-Based/dp/B0CV5T2YG6/?tag=theverge02-20" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;Amazon&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://howl.me/cmPHbMnH77Q"&gt;Best Buy&lt;/a&gt;, and the &lt;a href="https://www.anrdoezrs.net/links/8532386/type/dlg/sid/verge/https://store.google.com/us/product/fitbit_ace_lte?hl=en-US" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;Google Store&lt;/a&gt; through August 25th.&lt;/p&gt;
